Major project interface and flowechart;; 

User collection as doc with auto id
Account record and doc (sign in -- google)
Basic Info via Valid document
Verification status
Fraud check and scoring with AI
preferences
live status (is user is active -- checked.)
total booking history (as booking ids) in a list
orders; (cleaning, food order etc..) (stored as id)
present room (the present room user occupies -- as id of the room (room id))


Booking collection as doc with auto id
basic room details and styles
payment status
guest/ user who booked 
room in book (as id)
duration of booking and stay 
and other relevant info 
check in and check out records per day.
like a map; 

check in {entry1: 12pm, entry2: 3pm}
check out {entry1: 2pm, entry2: 6am}

the check in entry1 and check out entry 1 are in the same sequence. 
this would be in the user profile control in the admin hotel dashboard.. 

orders. (room service as id) as collection doc with auto id
type of order (food, drinks, drycleaning, massage, and more)
order details
order completion 
order status 
order payment status 

rooms collection as doc with auto id 
cleaning schedule 
cleaning status 
room style and details 
occupied or not.  


storage structure;;

rooms/{roomId}:
{
  roomId: "<doc-id>",
  title: "Ocean View Deluxe",
  roomType: "luxury",               // economy | standard | luxury
  pricePerDay: 23,550.0,               // number (currency)
  <!-- occupied: false,                  // boolean -->
  cleaningScheduleIndex: 3,         // number (your internal shift/day index)
  cleaningStatus: "not_cleaned",    // cleaned | not_cleaned
  features: ["tv", "fridge", "ac"], // array
  photoUrl: "https://...",          // string (or empty)
  createdAt: Timestamp,
  // optional availability calendar or rules...
}

bookings/{autoDocId}:
{
  bookId: "<same-as-doc-id>",        // set after creation or keep docRef.id client side
  paymentStatus: "pending",          // pending | paid | refunded | failed
  userId: "uid_abc123",
  roomBooked: "roomDocId",
  duration: "3 days",                // or "2 months 3 days" (string) â€” or keep structured {days:3, months:0}
  personalEffect: ["laptop", "suitcase"],
  // events array gives a complete history of checkin/checkout steps:
  events: [
    { type: "booking", step: "placed", done: true, ts: Timestamp, by: "uid_abc123" }
  ],
  status: "confirmed",               // pending | confirmed | checked_in | checked_out | cancelled
  createdAt: Timestamp,
  checkinSummary: {                  // optional quick-check snapshot
    entry1: true,
    entry2: true,
    entry3: false,
    lastCheckinAt: Timestamp
  },
  checkoutSummary: { ... }           // similar to checkinSummary
}
